JS cheat codes


Array 
1) slice(start, end) → non-mutating
     arr.slice(1, 4); // [index 1,2,3]
      arr.slice();    // copy array

2) splice(start, deleteCount, ...items) → mutates
  The splice() method of Array instances changes the contents of an array by removing or replacing
  existing elements and/or adding new elements in place

    arr.splice(2, 1);        // remove 1 element at index 2
    arr.splice(2, 0, 10);   // insert 10 at index 2
    arr.splice(1, 2, 5, 6); // replace 2 elements at 3
